General Rules for All Lessons:
- Each bullet point in the lesson outline must be expanded into 2–4 complete sentences.
- Use teaching-slide style: concise, clear, beginner-friendly.
- Always explain why the concept matters in microservices.
- Include short Spring Boot / Spring Cloud examples where relevant.
- Do NOT merge multiple concepts into a single bullet.
- Do not write essays or extremely minimal one-liners.


